deploy the demo app, create the gateway service, and deploy the ingress with the correct class routing through the second controller.\n\nLooking at the current controller configuration, it's using the default `k8s.io/ingress-nginx` class and watching all ingresses without a class. I need to change this to `ingress-1` and disable the catch-all behavior, then set up a separate `ingress-nginx-2` controller with the `ingress-2` class that will handle the demo ingress and route traffic to the demo app. Let me start by deploying the environment and running the test to verify everything works as expected.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5310,"cache_read_input_tokens":42227,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5310},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"unavailable"}},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f400d2d-3729-4634-bdef-100f534645c4","uuid":"5718bf89-7c15-4e6b-a749-b0ee259e1157","request_id":"req_011CcbyiC61HdVTyBuhLnEN6"}
